  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "IT Change and Release Analyst",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for Change Process governance and ensure all implementation adhere to the established process in terms of approval and documents to be attached.</li><li>Support application implementation and overseeing releases deliverables globally during different phases of development cycle and progression through various environments SIT, UAT and Production in a timely manner – includes scope monitoring and sign-off at various levels</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Key requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Knowledge of Change Control and Version Control and Deployment tools – Remedy Change Module, Endevor , Rocket RDOe and RDOi , ARCAD</li><li>Familiarity with supporting OCP platform and usage of DevOps Toolset  (Bitbucket , Jenkins & Jira workflows) will be an added advantage .</li><li>Basic CLP & RPG coding on the OS400 platform and scripting on linux operating system will be an added advantage</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Excel</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma / Degree in Computer Science or related field.</li><li>At least 3 years’ relevant experience preferably in a Finance Institution</li><li>Basic Technical knowledge in IT infrastructure, IT Change Management & Operations and OS400 systems is required</li><li>Process-oriented, strong analytical and communication skills</li><li>A team player with the ability in coordinating activities both within the team and across other teams</li><li>You are expected to ensure your work are adequately documented before executing in anyv environment.</li><li>Required to perform shift duties including weekend and public holidays where required.</li></ul>",
